🟢 Observer Pattern — Complete Explanation
🧠 1️⃣ Definition

Observer Pattern defines a one-to-many relationship, where when one object (subject) changes state, all its dependent objects (observers) are notified automatically.

🎯 Core Idea
One object changes
        ↓
All interested objects get notified automatically
🧩 2️⃣ Real-Life Examples

YouTube → Subscribers get notified when video uploaded

Stock market → Investors get price updates

E-commerce → “Notify me when product is back in stock”

WhatsApp → New message notification

